From 33f30cc67bd73f09c1a68f22fd4e5ffdd9085db5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 22:58:09 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(net): Clash API monitoring of subscription urltest
 selector
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 13 — surfaces which server in a VLESS subscription is currently
active and the last delay measurement for every server. Builds on
patch 12.

  * bridge.go: subscription sidecars now allocate a dedicated
    Clash API port + secret and embed
    experimental.clash_api.external_controller in the config.
    Single-server SingboxStart stays unchanged (no urltest, no
    selector to query). New exports SingboxGetClashPort and
    SingboxGetClashSecret. instance struct gets clashPort/clashSecret
    fields collected on start.
  * VlessBridge: Running gains clashPort+clashSecret, resolved by
    startAndCollect via the new exports. New public method
    clashEndpointForSubscription(key) returns {endpoint, secret} or
    nullopt when no sidecar is up.
  * SubscriptionMonitor (new) — small QObject that polls
    GET http://<endpoint>/proxies every 3 seconds with the bearer
    secret, parses sing-box's Clash response, picks the urltest
    selector tagged "proxy", and emits an rpl event with the
    currently active outbound tag plus per-server delay (-1 = unknown
    or timeout). Owned per ProxyBox dialog, started/stopped with it.
  * connection_box: when a Type::VlessSubscription dialog opens and
    the corresponding sidecar happens to be running, spin up the
    monitor. Header now also says "active: vN" or "monitor: <error>",
    and each server line is rendered as "→ 1. server-de  45ms" for
    the active one or "  2. server-nl  60ms" / "timeout" for the
    rest. Refresh resets the monitor (sidecar gets restarted on next
    use).
